examples.en: He recited the poem with great feeling.
He recited the poem in a solemn voice.
The patient recited a litany of complaints.
He recited the decree with an important air.
He recited the whole poem without a single trip.
She recited a poem that she had learnt at school.
The little girl self-consciously recited the poem.
The doctor recited the list of possible side effects of the drug.
Dorothea told him that she had seen Lydgate, and recited the gist of her conversation with him about the Hospital.
